---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Igor Samuk — tinkerer, builder, and chronic starter of weekend projects."
	pubDate={new Date('August 08 2021')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm Igor — a software developer by trade, a tinkerer by instinct. I've been writing code
		professionally for over twenty years, but the projects that actually excite me tend to happen
		at home, on weekends, in the basement, usually involving hardware that's doing something it
		wasn't quite designed to do.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is where I document those projects. Not tutorials, exactly — more like honest
		write-ups of what I was trying to do, what went wrong, and what I ended up with. I cover a
		lot of ground: home automation and IoT (I run a fairly involved Home Assistant setup),
		home lab infrastructure (Proxmox, TrueNAS, networking), occasional coding projects, and
		more recently, videography. The videography thing started as a way to document the other
		projects and turned into its own rabbit hole, as these things do.
	</p>

	<p>
		The name Makeventures is exactly what it sounds like — a log of making things, and the
		small adventures that come with it. Some projects take a weekend. Some have been running
		in the background for years. All of them taught me something, even when the something was
		"that was a complete waste of a Saturday."
	</p>

	<p>
		If something here is useful to you, I'm glad. If you spot an error or have a better way
		of doing something I've described, I'm always interested to hear it.
	</p>
</Layout>
